deigned his Cyprian charms to pour With lavish bounty over the child : Since wherever the siren moves along , In pleasing wonder chained is every tongue , Love's soft suffusion dims the aching eyes , Love's subtlest flame through every artery flies : Our trembling limbs the unequal pulse betray , We gaze in transport lost — then faint , and die away
